[src:1898-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1898-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1898-baltimore-orioles-season/1898-baltimore-orioles-season] The **1898 Baltimore Orioles season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1898-baltimore-orioles-season/1898-baltimore-orioles-season] Although there was no Temple Cup after the season, the Orioles still finished second in the National League for the second straight year with a record of 96–53, 6 games behind the Boston Beaneaters.
[src:1898-baltimore-orioles-season/1898-baltimore-orioles-season] The Orioles set a Major League record which still stands, for the most batters hit by a pitch in a season, with 148.
